<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D67FFBCFF63BA6C37938498" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D67FFBCFF63BA6C37548479" blockId="33.[189,303,1293,1319]" box="[189,303,1293,1319]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0E281D85D67FFBCFF63BA6C37548479" bold="true" box="[189,303,1293,1319]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D67FFBCFF63BA6C37548479" bold="true" box="[189,303,1293,1319]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D67FFBCFF63BA5D37938498" blockId="33.[189,1399,1340,1478]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
This species can be readily recognised among other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D67FFBCFC11BA5C320C8409" authorityName="Walker, 1849:" authorityYear="1157" box="[975,1143,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D67FFBCFC11BA5C320C8409" box="[975,1143,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Chersodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the modified abdominal tergite 2 which is broadened and thickened posteriorly. Abdominal modifications are quite common among 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D67FFBCFE59BAE7378D84FE" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1961" box="[391,502,1414,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Drapetini">Drapetini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D67FFBCFDD6BAE7356A84FE" author="Shamshev I. V. &amp; Grootaert P." box="[520,785,1414,1440]" journalOrPublisher="The Natural History Journal of Chulalongkorn University" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="27 - 32" part="6" refId="ref70642" refString="Shamshev I. V. &amp; Grootaert P. 2006. Description of new species of Stilpon Loew (Diptera: Hybotidae) from Cambodia. The Natural History Journal of Chulalongkorn University 6: 27 - 32." title="Description of new species of Stilpon Loew (Diptera: Hybotidae) from Cambodia" type="journal article" year="2006">
Shamshev 
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D67FFBCFD52BAE634B284FE" box="[652,713,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D67FFBCFCFEBAE732F284FF" author="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" box="[800,1161,1414,1441]" firstAuthor="Grootaert" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="165 - 174" refId="ref69293" refString="Grootaert P. &amp; Shamshev I. 2009 b. New species of the genus Elaphropeza Macquart (Diptera: Hybotidae) with remarkable abdominal structures from Viet Nam. Studia dipterologica 15 (2008): 165 - 174." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="b">Grootaert &amp; Shamshev 2009b</bibRefCitation>
) but this is the first record for 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D67FFBCFEE7BACA379A849B" authorityName="Walker, 1849:" authorityYear="1157" box="[313,481,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D67FFBCFEE7BACA379A849B" box="[313,481,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Chersodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
